<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1627344-i-ve-not-finished-the-book-but-i-m">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I've not finished the book but I'm bothered why the author did not go into more detail on how Elwood was convicted of that crime. Couldn't he have been absolved by his teacher and others, like his employer? I understand that blacks were not given anything close to fair treatment but simply having Elwood go from being in a stolen car to the Nickel "school" seems to be lacking more explanation. Comments? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1627344'><a id="like_count_community_question_1627344" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1627344?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F42270835-the-nickel-boys">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1627344-i-ve-not-finished-the-book-but-i-m">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1627344-i-ve-not-finished-the-book-but-i-m">See all 11 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
