  <span id="freeText9962431866339581280" style="display:none">What's happening? Why was I bored by a book so many loved, especially since its subject should have affected me a great deal? The introduction was promising. The novel itself left me disconnected and detached, not to mention I had this nagging feeling that I'd read this story before. <br />The writing was straight forward if I'm being honest, I expected it to be a bit more literary.<br />The story is important, kudos to Whitehead for bringing it to our attention. My brain was, of course, horrified, but my heart was only half melted.<br /><br />Another book I feel I should have loved but didn't. <br /><br /><br /></span>
